Program: Discovery
Title: The lives of ants
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryf5
Last Broadcast Date: 18 June 2003
Could army ants teach us how to run our congested roads and cities? The programme explores how ants manage to live successfully without a central control system. Learning about ants could also help us interpret important commercial medical data and even help us to understand how the human brain works. Presented by Peter Evans. Show less